This laboratory course helps students gain skills they need to carry out both standard measurements and complex experiments that require acquainting with electrical measuring instruments and methods of measurement.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the laboratory course is to give basic knowledge about the most essential measuring instruments, measurement techniques and experimental methods in the field of electricity and magnetism.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students who have taken the course are expected:
*  to know and explain basic physical laws and principles of the electromagnetics;
*  to be able to use most essential electrical measuring instruments;
*  to assemble an experimental set-up for electrical measurements planned;
*  to learn the fundamental knowledge in the area of electrical safety;
*  to be skilled in data processing and executing the report of measurements using the software package MathCAD.
